A short statement from each student (max. 300 words) about an interesting problem they solved, or an interesting solution they devised, as part of their work. 

 

Danny -  When I was writing the code for the game manager, I ran into a problem where the ball would sometimes get stuck on the lane and not hit any pins, or it wouldn’t hit any pins and the game would think that the round was still going on, making it unable to progress. To fix this I added a check using a coroutine called CheckBallStopped(). After a small delay it checks the balls speed (if it has dropped below a certain threshold). The solution was easy but it made a big difference in the gameplay and I am happy with myself that I managed to sort it. It made sure that the game moved smoothly, even if the ball didn't hit any pins. 
